Information about the algorithm to read live logs from. The /live/logs/read API accepts requests in the following format:

ReadLiveLogsRequest Model - Request to read the logs of a specific algorithm. The difference between 'startLine' and 'endLine' must be smaller than 250, else an error will be thrown.
format object
example: json
Format of the log results.
projectId integer
required
example: 23456789
Project Id of the live running algorithm.
algorithmId string
required
Deploy Id (Algorithm Id) of the live running algorithm.
startLine integer
required
Start line of logs to read.
endLine integer
required
End line of logs to read.
Example 
{
  "format": "json",
  "projectId": 23456789,
  "algorithmId": "string",
  "startLine": 0,
  "endLine": 0
}
